<subSubSection id="1FE5655FFFE7416ACAD1ED7CFEED2416" pageId="17" pageNumber="468" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="574036D4FFE7416ACAD1ED7CFEED2416" blockId="17.[151,1437,1040,1282]" pageId="17" pageNumber="468">
The only known male specimen of 
<taxonomicName id="90FF4D57FFE7416AC861ED7CFCB2244F" box="[551,768,1040,1067]" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" genus="Enyaliopsis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="468" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="undefined-3">
<emphasis id="658BEAC6FFE7416AC861ED7CFD18244F" box="[551,682,1040,1066]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="468">Enyaliopsis</emphasis>
spec. 3
</taxonomicName>
is medium-sized and comparatively slender built. The pronotum is spiny and similar to 
<taxonomicName id="90FF4D57FFE7416ACBA3ED59FDE2242B" baseAuthorityName="Lucas" baseAuthorityYear="1885" box="[485,592,1076,1102]" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" genus="Enyaliopsis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="468" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bloyeti">
<emphasis id="658BEAC6FFE7416ACBA3ED59FDE2242B" box="[485,592,1076,1102]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="468">E. bloyeti</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. However, 
<taxonomicName id="90FF4D57FFE7416AC894ED59FC8F242B" baseAuthorityName="Lucas" baseAuthorityYear="1885" box="[722,829,1076,1102]" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" genus="Enyaliopsis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="468" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bloyeti">
<emphasis id="658BEAC6FFE7416AC894ED59FC8F242B" box="[722,829,1076,1102]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="468">E. bloyeti</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is generally much larger in size with a broad and thus stouter pronotum.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
