<subSubSection id="1FE5655FFFE7416ACA81EDA8FE2F2567" pageId="17" pageNumber="468" type="description">
<paragraph id="574036D4FFE7416ACA81EDA8FE2F2567" blockId="17.[151,1437,1040,1282]" pageId="17" pageNumber="468">
<emphasis id="658BEAC6FFE7416ACA81EDA8FE8F24BB" bold="true" box="[199,317,1220,1246]" pageId="17" pageNumber="468">Genitalia.</emphasis>
The titillator (
<figureCitation id="CFC42A51FFE7416ACBAEEDA8FDF124BB" box="[488,579,1220,1246]" captionStart="FIGURE 9" captionStartId="13.[151,250,1200,1224]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,237,1177]" captionTargetId="figure-41@13.[151,1436,237,1179]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURE 9. Titillator and genitalic sclerites in Hetrodini, Enyaliopsina. First row A Cosmoderus femoralis (CH8627), B Enyaliopsis bloyeti (Kazimzumbwi), C Enyaliopsis carolinus (Minziro), D Enyaliopsis ephippiatus (Rau Forest); second row E Enyaliopsis spec. 1 near ephippiatus (Mwala), F Enyaliopsis jennae (Uluguru), G Enyaliopsis spec. 2 (Mpwapwa), H Enyaliopsis spec. 3 (East Chenene); third row I Gymnoproctus rammei (Puge Simbo), J Gymnoproctus spec. (East Chenene)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6392735" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6392735/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="468">Fig. 9H</figureCitation>
) is triangular and small as found in several other 
<taxonomicName id="90FF4D57FFE7416ACECEEDA8FAD424BB" box="[1160,1382,1220,1246]" pageId="17" pageNumber="468">
<emphasis id="658BEAC6FFE7416ACECEEDA8FAB924BB" box="[1160,1291,1220,1246]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="468">Enyaliopsis</emphasis>
species
</taxonomicName>
(see figures in 
<bibRefCitation id="336E4B25FFE7416ACB4FED84FE222567" author="Glenn, G. S. Jr." box="[265,400,1256,1282]" pageId="17" pageNumber="468" pagination="67 - 102" refId="ref16270" refString="Glenn, G. S. Jr. (1991) A systematic revision of Enyaliopsis Karsch 1887 (Orthoptera: Tettigoniidae, Hetrodinae). Transactions of the American Entomological Society, 117, 67 - 102. http: // www. jstor. org / stable / 25078540" type="journal article" year="1991">Glenn 1991</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
